@startuml
' @id(SEQ-RUN-CYCLE)
' @ref(USE-RUN-CYCLE)
'
' Objective-side runtime flow of the new single-description orchestration
' skill. It selects the entry point, owns the cycle boundary, and loops
' the implement/review cycle to parity, pausing for clarification.
'
' @desc(SEQ-RUN-CYCLE, "How /mdd-cycle drives one full MDD loop: pick entry, open+snapshot the cycle, loop generate/map->validate->implement->map->validate->review until parity, then close+diff.")
title Run a full MDD cycle from one description (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "/mdd-cycle\n(orchestration skill)" as Orch
database ".mdd/cycles/<n>/\n(manifest, before/, after/)" as Store
participant "/mdd-generate\nor /mdd-map" as Entry
participant "/mdd-validate" as Val
participant "/mdd-implement" as Impl
participant "/mdd-map" as Map
participant "/mdd-review" as Rev

Dev -> Orch : /mdd-cycle [description?]

alt description provided
  Orch -> Orch : entry = generate
else no description
  Orch -> Orch : entry = map\n(behave as /mdd-map with no comments)
end

Orch -> Store : open cycle N\nsnapshot .mdd/models/current/ -> before/
Store --> Orch : cycle N opened (status=Open)

Orch -> Entry : run entry skill (scoped to description)
alt entry == generate
  note right of Entry
    Authors objective models + @desc per
    significant @id. Marks ambiguity in the
    model instead of inventing behavior.
  end note
end
Entry --> Orch : models written

loop until /mdd-review parity matches
  Orch -> Val : /mdd-validate
  alt validation errors
    Val --> Orch : errors
    Orch -> Impl : (only when both sides non-empty)
  else clean
    Val --> Orch : clean
  end

  opt decision is genuinely ambiguous
    Orch -> Dev : ask clarifying question(s)
    Dev --> Orch : answer
    note right of Orch
      Mandatory pause. The skill NEVER guesses
      an ambiguous modeling/implementation
      decision; it blocks on the user.
    end note
  end

  Orch -> Impl : /mdd-implement (write code)
  Impl --> Orch : code changed
  Orch -> Map : /mdd-map (refresh current + @desc)
  Map --> Orch : current refreshed
  Orch -> Val : /mdd-validate
  Val --> Orch : clean
  Orch -> Rev : /mdd-review (ID + security parity)
  alt mismatch
    Rev --> Orch : .diff.puml / .security.diff.puml
  else match
    Rev --> Orch : parity closed
  end
end

Orch -> Store : snapshot current/ -> after/\nwrite <diagram>.diff.puml\nclose cycle N (status=Closed)
Store --> Orch : cycle N closed
Orch --> Dev : cycle N complete (summary + diff ready)
@enduml
